rest_of_day_open: Since the week is halfway over, and I have so much to do for work, I think it is going to feel like it is flying by even though ironically I don't want it to because I need to get a bunch of things done to make the different deadlines I have. Overall, I think it will be positive otherwise and I will be successful in making those deadlines.
critical_positive: What worked best is we found something we had in common almost immediately - we both have dogs. This only happened because his dog appeared on screen and I asked for her name and how old she was. We talked about how many pets each of us had and that opened the door to funny stories about the dogs, how the dogs eat, and what they do. The rest of the conversation flowed well after that.
critical_negative: I think we would have had a rougher start to the conversation if his dog hadn't come up on the screen. During moments of silence, it was clearly about to get awkward before one of us brought up either the same subject or a slightly different one. Towards the end we got on a roll.

rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week is wide open.  The weather is looking good, and I've got plans scheduled with friends for a couple of nights later in the week.  The worst of the weather predicted for this week has past, and despite it getting chilly I'm looking forward to some sunny days.
critical_positive: We both had something in common (pets) and when my dog walked in front of the camera it immediately gave us a fun shared topic of conversation.  It can sometimes be difficult to come up with things of interest that allow back and forth communication when meeting a stranger, but this let us share stories about our pets.
critical_negative: It's hard to point at anything that didn't go well in the conversation.  We had a good flow back and forth, and even when unpleasant topics like Covid came up we didn't get bogged down in anything unpleasant for too long and were able to circle back around to more fun topics.
